<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Picea sitchensis </i>has relatively thin bark and shallow roots, and is very susceptible to mortality from fire. Many stands develop in moist to wet areas that are not associated with fire on stream bottoms or on seepy slopes. Fire intervals are long (150-350+ years). Fires are severe when they occur and result in stand replacement (Parminter 1991). After a fire, off-site, unburned trees provide wind-dispersed seed to re-colonize.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
